<DIV class=3Dblogentry>
<H1><A class=3DentryTitle=20
href=3D"http://tirania.org/blog/archive/2008/May-06-1.html">Cross-platfor=
m,=20
standalone Silverilght Applications</A></H1>
<P>Tamir Khason <A=20
href=3D"http://blogs.microsoft.co.il/blogs/tamir/archive/2008/05/02/stand=
-alone-multiplatform-silverlight-application.aspx">published=20
an interesting approach</A> at hosting standalone Silverlight =
applications.=20
<P>His solution is a Windows.Forms application that hosts a=20
Windows.Forms.WebControl and inside the WebControl he hosts Silverlight. =

<P>Unlike <A =
href=3D"http://tirania.org/blog/archive/2008/Apr-17.html">my=20
proposal</A> for standalone Silverlight Applications that is currently=20
Moonlight-specific (and currently limited to Linux/X11) this approach =
works on=20
Windows with .NET and with Linux using Mono and Moonlight:=20
<CENTER><IMG=20
src=3D"http://primates.ximian.com/~miguel/pictures/image_bd3dfa68-9af8-41=
c0-bb75-eb150c3500eb.png">=20

<P><I>Left side: .NET hosting WebControl and Silverlight on Windows; =
Right side:=20
Mono hosting WebControl and Moonlight running on Linux.</I> </CENTER>
<P>In addition to hosting the WebControl for hosting Silverlight, a =
thread is=20
running to dispatch http requests locally using HttpListener. =
HttpListener is an=20
embeddable HTTP server that is part of the class libraries, and exposes =
a very=20
limited API. You can host ASP.NET with HttpListener by doing the =
bindings by=20
hand, or you could use our Mono.WebServer library (part of our =
XSP/mod_mono=20
distribution) to allow your applications to have a fully hosted ASP.NET =
server.=20
<P>Mono.WebServer is what <A =
href=3D"http://www.ifolder.com/">iFolder</A> uses to=20
embed the ASP.NET server to expose SOAP-based WebServices to clients.=20
<P>Of course, this currently does not work on MacOS X as we do have no=20
implementation of WebControl for Windows.Forms on OSX, something that a=20
contributor might want to look into.=20
<P>You can get the source for the sample from <A=20
href=3D"http://blogs.microsoft.co.il/blogs/tamir/archive/2008/05/02/stand=
-alone-multiplatform-silverlight-application.aspx">Tamir's=20
page</A>.=20
